Project Title: NodeJS Web Application Development

Aim: Construct a web application using NodeJS, ExpressJS, MongoDB, Mongoose, and EJS.

1. Day 1-2: Planning and Design
- Identify the needs for the application - Create the database structure
- Arrange the project's hierarchy.

2. Backend implementation (Days 3–4)
To store data, integrate MongoDB and Mongoose. -Set up NodeJS and ExpressJS.
- Create controller and route files.

3. Frontend implementation (Days 5–6)
-Use UI design -Incorporate EJS templating -Customise appearance using CSS

4. Testing (Days 7-8)
-Evaluate frontend and backend components using unit testing -Conduct integration testing

5. Day 9–10: Documentation & Deployment
-Record functionality and code.
-Install the finished program.

